<chapter id="fixes" xreflabel="List of Fixes">

<title>Fixes Included in the Service Pack Roll</title>

<para>
	Area51 Roll
</para>

<itemizedlist>

<listitem>
	<para>
	The <emphasis>tripwire</emphasis> package is now included.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Tripwire reports are now correctly generated.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	The tripwire <emphasis>email to</emphasis> is now correctly read
	from the database.
	</para>
</listitem>

</itemizedlist>


<para>
	Base Roll
</para>

<itemizedlist>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Fixes the <emphasis>greceptor</emphasis> bug that causes a traceback
	that looks like:
	</para>

<para>
<screen>
 greceptor warning: greceptor: got a metric with a strange type (22)
------greceptor last traceback----
Traceback (most recent call last):

  File "/opt/rocks/lib/python2.4/site-packages/gmon/reporter.py", line 203, in run
    metric = gmon.Gmetric.parse(msg)

error: got a metric with a strange type (22)
</screen>
</para>

</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	The <emphasis>authpriv</emphasis> entry in the logrotate configuration
	file is fixed.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	The <emphasis>authpriv</emphasis> entry in the logrotate configuration
	file is fixed.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Fixed replace node in <emphasis>insert-ethers</emphasis>.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	<emphasis>snmpd</emphasis> syslog messages are now greatly reduced.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	The command <emphasis>rocks run host</emphasis> now obeys the
	<emphasis>managed</emphasis> boolean flag.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Rewrite pxelinux.cfg for a host after setting the run/install action.
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	If a host has an alias set in the database, include that alias in
	/etc/hosts.
	</para>
</listitem>

</itemizedlist>


<para>
	Ganglia Roll
</para>

<itemizedlist>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Put Rocks-defined metrics back in the roll (e.g., cluster top and
	queue stats).
	</para>
</listitem>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Backend nodes now send their metrics to the frontend with unicast
	rather than multicast.
	The frontend still sends multicast messages to the backend nodes
	(in order for the frontend to collect 'metadata' from the nodes'
	metrics).
	</para>
</listitem>

</itemizedlist>


<para>
	Xen Roll
</para>

<itemizedlist>

<listitem>
	<para>
	Fixes to support virtual compute nodes that are managed by a
	physical frontend.
	</para>
</listitem>

</itemizedlist>


</chapter>
